Yes — I’d call the next piece Phase 3B.

Phase 3A added the profile framework but kept future profiles hidden.

Phase 3B should expose the future profile sets in the PXE menu as safe placeholders only. That means users can see:

Minimal Installs
Security Baseline Installs
Security + LUKS Installs
Small Disk Installs
Developer Workstation Installs
Embedded / Edge Hardware Installs
Utilities / Rescue
Drop to iPXE shell

…but only Minimal Installs actually boots anything. The other profile menus should say something like “Profile not implemented yet” and return to the main menu. No new kickstarts yet. No new boot targets yet. No role/bootstrap changes yet.

Edit 1 — scripts/generate-pxe-content.py

Find your PROFILE_DEFINITIONS section.

For each future profile, change this:

implemented=False,
show_in_main_menu=False,

to this:

implemented=False,
show_in_main_menu=True,

So the future profiles become visible but still non-booting.

You can also update the comment above them to this:

    # Future profile sets.
    # These are visible in Phase 3B as safe placeholders only.
    # implemented=False prevents boot targets and kickstarts from being generated.

Edit 2 — improve status.json

In render_status(), add these variables before status = { ... }:

    visible_profiles = [
        profile.profile_id
        for profile in PROFILE_DEFINITIONS
        if profile.show_in_main_menu
    ]
    enabled_profiles = [
        profile.profile_id
        for profile in PROFILE_DEFINITIONS
        if profile.show_in_main_menu and profile.implemented
    ]
    unimplemented_profiles = [
        profile.profile_id
        for profile in PROFILE_DEFINITIONS
        if profile.show_in_main_menu and not profile.implemented
    ]

Then replace this part:

        "enabled_profiles": [
            profile.profile_id
            for profile in PROFILE_DEFINITIONS
            if profile.show_in_main_menu and profile.implemented
        ],

with this:

        "visible_profiles": visible_profiles,
        "enabled_profiles": enabled_profiles,
        "unimplemented_profiles": unimplemented_profiles,

That will make the status clearer. You should see minimal in enabled_profiles, and the other Phase 3 profile sets in unimplemented_profiles.

What should change after Phase 3B

Expected changes:

boot.ipxe      changes
status.json    changes
isos.txt       should not change
rhel8-minimal.ks should not change

