  -o /tmp/pxe-phase3b/status.json
curl -fss http://127.0.0.1:18080/ks/rhel8-minimal.ks \
  -o /tmp/pxe-phase3b/rhel8-minimal.ks
curl -fss -o /dev/null http://127.0.0.1:18080/ui/background.png
curl -fss -o /dev/null http://127.0.0.1:18080/rhel8/images/pxeboot/vmlinuz
curl -fss -o /dev/null http://127.0.0.1:18080/rhel8/images/pxeboot/initrd.img

Then compare against Phase 3A:

diff -u /tmp/pxe-phase3a/isos.txt /tmp/pxe-phase3b/isos.txt
diff -u /tmp/pxe-phase3a/rhel8-minimal.ks /tmp/pxe-phase3b/rhel8-minimal.ks
diff -u /tmp/pxe-phase3a/boot.ipxe /tmp/pxe-phase3b/boot.ipxe
diff -u /tmp/pxe-phase3a/status.json /tmp/pxe-phase3b/status.json

The first two diffs should be empty. The last two should show the new visible placeholder profiles.

Also run:

grep -n "Security Baseline\|Security + LUKS\|Small Disk\|Developer Workstation\|Embedded" /tmp/pxe-phase3b/boot.ipxe
grep -n "Profile not implemented yet" /tmp/pxe-phase3b/boot.ipxe
grep -n "rhel8_security\|rhel9_security\|rhel10_security\|rhel8_developer\|rhel9_developer\|rhel10_developer" /tmp/pxe-phase3b/boot.ipxe || true

The first two should find matches. The last one should find nothing. That proves the profile menus are visible, but they are not accidentally bootable yet.